   "id": "70f0961a"
    "---\n",
    "## 1. The Mechanism: First-Mover Bias Confirmed (Paper 5.1)\n",
    "\n",
    "The central question: does sequential residual dependency cause SHAP instability?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Controlled comparison**: DASH and LSM both use the same low `colsample_bytree` (0.1-0.5)\n",
    "and the same total compute budget. The only difference is that DASH's models are trained\n",
    "independently, while LSM's trees are trained sequentially on modified residuals.\n",
    "\n",
    "If first-mover bias is the cause, LSM should be the **worst** method (sequential dependency\n",
    "amplifies it) and DASH should be immune (independence cancels it)."
   ]
